
## Custom CNN (193 Image Dataset)
Dataset
Total Images: 193
Original 159 labeled images
Additional manually labeled capacitor images

Class Distribution:
Bottom : 42
Left   : 61
Right  : 37
Top    : 53

Test Accuracy:

47.62%
Confusion Matrix:

[[2 3 0 1]
 [1 4 0 0]
 [1 2 0 1]
 [0 2 0 4]]

Observations
Accuracy dropped significantly after increasing the dataset size.
The model struggled to learn the Right class.
Several misclassifications occurred between neighboring orientations.
Rotation testing showed that the model often ignored image rotation.
Inference

The simple CNN architecture was unable to generalize well on the more diverse dataset. Increasing the dataset size alone did not improve performance.

## MobileNetV2 (Frozen)
Test Accuracy:

76.19%
Confusion Matrix:

[[5 0 0 1]
 [0 5 0 0]
 [0 1 3 0]
 [0 1 2 3]]

Observations
Large improvement over the custom CNN on the 193-image dataset.
Successfully learned the Right class.
Produced more meaningful confidence scores.
Showed partial orientation awareness during rotation testing.
Performance remained stable on several unseen capacitor images.
Inference

Transfer learning significantly improved performance. The pretrained MobileNetV2 features generalized much better than the custom CNN.

## MobileNetV2 (Fine-Tuned)
Configuration
Last MobileNetV2 layers unfrozen
Learning Rate: 1e-5
Early Stopping enabled

Test Accuracy:

76.19%
Confusion Matrix:

[[5 0 0 1]
 [0 5 0 0]
 [0 1 3 0]
 [0 1 2 3]]

Observations
Fine-tuning did not improve accuracy.
Confusion matrix remained unchanged.
Class performance remained unchanged.
Inference

The dataset size is likely the primary limitation. MobileNetV2 had already extracted most useful information from the available training data, and additional fine-tuning provided no measurable benefit.

Overall Conclusions
Transfer learning substantially outperformed a custom CNN architecture.
Increasing dataset size alone did not guarantee better performance.
MobileNetV2 achieved the best balance between accuracy and generalization.
Rotation testing revealed that orientation learning remains imperfect and can be affected by capacitor symmetry.
The current bottleneck is dataset diversity and size rather than model architecture.
